ormUSA}} |Richard Overton\n|{{Party shading/ReformUSA}} |[[Reform Party (United States)|Reform]]\n|{{party shading/ReformUSA}} |2,788\n|{{party shading/ReformUSA}} |2%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House election, 2004|2004]]\n||\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |'''Fred Upton'''\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |197,425\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |65%\n|\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |Scott Elliott\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |97,978\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |32%\n|\n|{{party shading/Green}} |Randall MacPhee\n|{{party shading/Green}} |[[Green Party (United States)|Green]]\n|{{party shading/Green}} |2,311\n|{{party shading/Green}} |1%\n|\n|{{party shading/Libertarian}} |Erwin Haas\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |[[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]]\n|{{party shading/Libertarian}} |2,275\n|{{party shading/Libertarian}} |1%\n|\n|{{party shading/Constitution}} |W. Dennis FitzSimons\n|{{Party shading/Constitution}} |[[U.S. Taxpayers Party of Michigan|USTPM]]\n|{{party shading/Constitution}} |2,169\n|{{Party shading/Constitution}} |1%\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House election, 2006|2006]]\n||\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |'''Fred Upton'''\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |142,125\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |61%\n|\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |[[Kim Clark (candidate)|Kim Clark]]\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |88,978\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |38%\n|\n|{{party shading/Libertarian}} |Kenneth Howe\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |[[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]]\n|{{party shading/Libertarian}} |3,480\n|{{party shading/Libertarian}} |1%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House election, 2008|2008]]\n||\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |'''Fred Upton'''\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |188,157\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |59%\n|\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |[[Don Cooney]]\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |123,257\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |39%\n|\n|{{party shading/Libertarian